The paper deals with algorithmic problems on graphs, specifically those parameterized by treedepth. This suggests that the paper could belong to categories related to graph algorithms and parameterized complexity. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) are both relevant categories for this paper. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also a possibility, as the paper discusses time and space complexity of algorithms. cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) are less likely but still possible categories, as they both deal with graph-related problems.
